#Define Model
inputs=Input(shape=(187, 1)) # number of Input Features, n_x =28
# Feature extraction
x=Conv1D(32, kernel_size=(3,), activation="relu") (inputs)
x=MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(2,))(x)
x=Conv1D(64, kernel_size=(3,), activation="relu") (x)
x=MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(2,))(x)
# Flattening Layer
flat=Flatten()(x)
# Regression Layer
d=Dense(40, activation="relu")(flat)
output=Dense(5, activation="softmax")(d)
model= Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=output)
model.summary()

def LSTMModel(seq_length=187, depth=1, n_class=5):

    model3 = tf.keras.Sequential()
    model3.add(Bidirectional(LSTM(64), input_shape=(seq_length, depth)))
    model3.add(Dropout(rate=0.25))
    model3.add(Dense(n_class, activation="softmax"))

    return model3

model_bilstm =  LSTMModel(seq_length=187, depth=1, n_class=5)
model_bilstm.summary()

#Define Alexnet Model
def get_1DCNNmodel(n_x):
    inputs=Input(shape=(n_x,1)) ### n_x=187
    ### Feature extraction
    x=Conv1D(32, kernel_size=(3,), activation="relu") (inputs)
    x=MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(3,))(x)
    x=Conv1D(64, kernel_size=(3,), activation="relu") (x)
    x=MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(3,))(x)
    x=Conv1D(120, kernel_size=(1,), activation="relu") (x)
    ## Flattening Layer
    flat=Flatten()(x)
    ## Classification Layer
    d=Dense(150, activation="relu")(flat)
    d=Dense(250, activation="relu")(d)
    d=Dropout(0.5)(d)
    # d=Dense(30, activation="relu")(d)
    # d=Dropout(0.2)(d)
    output=Dense(5, activation="softmax")(d)
    model2= Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=output)
    # lossfn=tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=False,ignore_class=None,
    # reduction=losses_utils.ReductionV2.AUTO, name='sparse_categorical_crossentropy')
    model2.compile(loss="categorical_crossentropy", metrics=["accuracy"], optimizer="adam")
    # model.compile(loss="sparse_categorical_crossentropy", metrics=["accuracy"], optimizer="adam")
    return model2

## Calling AlexNet model function
model5 = get_1DCNNmodel(187)
model5.summary()

def DeepResidualModel(seq_length=187, depth=1, n_class=5):

    inputs = tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=(seq_length, depth))

    out1 = tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, strides=1)(inputs)

    for _ in range(4):

        out = tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, strides=1, padding='same')(out1)
        out = tf.keras.layers.Activation("relu")(out)
        out = tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, strides=1, padding='same')(out)
        out = tf.keras.layers.Add()([out, out1])
        out = tf.keras.layers.Activation("relu")(out)
        out1 = tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling1D(pool_size=5, strides=2)(out)

    out = tf.keras.layers.Flatten()(out1)
    out = tf.keras.layers.Dense(32)(out)
    out = tf.keras.layers.Activation("relu")(out)
    out = tf.keras.layers.Dense(32)(out)
    out = tf.keras.layers.Dense(n_class)(out)
    out = tf.keras.layers.Softmax()(out)

    return tf.keras.Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=out)

model6 = DeepResidualModel(seq_length=187, depth=1, n_class=5)
